/**
 * Oncoprint behavioral suite — port of
 * end-to-end-test/remote/specs/core/oncoprint.spec.js.
 *
 * Unlike oncoprint-screenshot.spec.ts (visual regressions) and
 * oncoprint-gaps.spec.ts (gap rendering), this file exercises *logical*
 * oncoprint behavior: sample/patient sort order, track counts, legend
 * contents, and clustering-state UI indicators. Assertions are made
 * against the page DOM or against `window.frontendOnc`, not screenshots.
 *
 * Only one test ("merged tracks") takes a screenshot — the expanded
 * merged-track layout is fiddly enough that a DOM assertion would be
 * brittle, so we keep the visual check there.
 *
 * Long id-order strings are extracted to the `ID_ORDERS` block at the
 * top. They are intentionally verbatim — each one is a canonical
 * ordering fingerprint, so a regression that reorders samples will fail
 * here even if the visual screenshot still matches.
 */

